author: Alyssa Schneider
title: Fake field goal makes the difference in No. 6 LSU's 35-28 victory over No. 8 Florida
text:
Fake field goal makes the difference in No. 6 LSU's 35-28 victor - KPLC 7 News, Lake Charles, Louisiana Member Center: Live Blog LSU Tigers Football Scoreboard Fake field goal makes the difference in No. 6 LSU's 35-28 victory over No. 8 Florida Posted: Trent Domingue and his teammates celebrate the touchdown on a trick play. (Source: WAFB) BATON ROUGE, LA (WAFB) - 
If viewing this story on a mobile device or in an email, click the link for postgame coverage, including LSU head coach Les Miles' news conference - http://shout.lt/bf54r , LSU player interviews - http://shout.lt/bf54M 
No. 6 LSU used a fake field goal to get past No. 8 Florida, 35-28 and remain unbeaten. The Tigers hand the Gators their first lost of the season. 
Running back Leonard Fournette accounted for two of LSU's five touchdowns and had 180 rushing yards in the first two quarters. 
LSU quarterback Brandon Harris was 13 of 19 for 202 yards with 2 touchdown passes to wide receiver Malachi Dupre, including a 50-yard pass with 15 seconds left in the second quarter. 
LSU kicker Trent Domingue scored a touchdown in the fourth quarter, faking a field goal and running 16 yards into the endzone to give LSU the win, 35-28. 
Harris was coming off the best game of his career against South Carolina with 228 yards passing and 2 touchdowns. But the Gamecocks are 0-4 in the SEC and their defense ranks dead last in the conference. 
Florida's defense presents a much different set of challenges, ranked near the top of the SEC and very opportunistic when the ball is in the air. 
Scoring Plays: 
Florida quarterback Treon Harris threw to Jake McGee for a 4-yard TD. (Florida 7, LSU 0 - 10:13 1st Qtr) 
LSU running back Leonard Fournette rushed for a 2-yard TD. (LSU 7, Florida 7 - 12:23 2nd Qtr) 
LSU quarterback Brandon Harris threw to Malachi Dupre for a 9-yard TD. (LSU 14, Florida 7 - 5:00 2nd Qtr) 
LSU's Fournette ran 6 yards for a TD. (LSU 21, Florida 7 - 2:25 2nd Qtr) 
Florida's Harris connected with McGee for 19-yard TD. (LSU 21, Florida 14 - 1:35 2nd Qtr) 
LSU's Harris passed to Dupre for a 50-yard TD. (LSU 28, Florida 14 - 0:15 2nd Qtr) 
Florida's Kelvin Taylor rushed for a 2-yard TD. (LSU 28, Florida 21 - 8:03 3rd Qtr) 
Florida's Antonio Callaway returned a punt 72 yards for a TD. (LSU 28, Florida 28 - 1:04 3rd Qtr) 
LSU kicker Trent Domingue rushed 16 yards for a TD after faking a FG. (LSU 35, Florida 28 - 10:40 4th Qtr)
